<h1 class="ds-page-title">Charts</h1>
<p class="ds-page-lead">
    Charts visualise data to help users understand trends and patterns.
</p>

<h2>Pie chart</h2>
<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example - Pie chart (conceptual)</div>
    <p>Pie charts show proportions of a whole. Use libraries like Chart.js for implementation.</p>
    <div style="text-align: center; padding: 2rem; background: #f6f8fa; border-radius: 8px;">
        <p><em>Pie chart visualisation would appear here</em></p>
    </div>
</div>

<h2>Bar chart</h2>
<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example - Bar chart (conceptual)</div>
    <p>Bar charts compare values across categories. Use libraries like Chart.js for implementation.</p>
    <div style="text-align: center; padding: 2rem; background: #f6f8fa; border-radius: 8px;">
        <p><em>Bar chart visualisation would appear here</em></p>
    </div>
</div>

<h2>Usage guidelines</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Choose appropriate chart types for your data</li>
    <li>Ensure charts are accessible (provide text alternatives)</li>
    <li>Use consistent colours across charts</li>
    <li>Include clear labels and legends</li>
</ul>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Provide text alternatives for chart data</li>
    <li>Ensure sufficient colour contrast</li>
    <li>Don't rely on colour alone to convey information</li>
    <li>Include descriptive titles and labels</li>
</ul>
